{
  "_notes": [
    "Reference config cloned from Nabataea_art_reference_v1.json for the Teutonic Order PNG pack.",
    "Extract Teutonic_Order.zip into C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/. The ZIP contains a Teutonic_Order folder, so the final PNG paths should be C:/Repos/PNGtoDDSConverter/Input/Teutonic_Order/*.png.",
    "mod_data_dir is intentionally omitted so check/build can run before the mod folder exists. Use --mod-data-dir in PowerShell when importing into an installed mod.",
    "PowerShell check: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\TeutonicOrder_art_reference_v1.json --check-only",
    "PowerShell build: py -3 .\\universal_civ5_pipeline_spartan_artfix_v9.py --config .\\TeutonicOrder_art_reference_v1.json",
    "Normal and alpha icons use the Spartan League v8 footprint: 0.65625 of each cell, so 256px cells get about 168px visible art.",
    "Unit flags are kept on the separate Civ V unit-flag profile, not the normal circular-icon footprint.",
    "Normal atlas index map: 0 civ, 1 leader, 2 TeutonicArcher, 3 TeutonicSwordsman, 4 TeutonicTown, 5 CrusaderFervor, 6 TeutonicBulwark.",
    "Black-background glyph sources retain their _black filename suffix and are processed through black-to-transparent glyph profiles.",
    "HermannVonSalza_Scene.png is 1672x941, so this config uses civ5_leader_scene_16x9 rather than civ5_leader_scene_4x3."
  ],
